          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>
                                        <date>June 4 1853</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Reverend Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>Phia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I have received all<lb/> your letters &amp; would
                                        have long<lb/> since replied but for the<lb/> large amount
                                        of anxiety &amp;<lb/> unhappiness produced by the<lb/>
                                        crisis &amp; its effects which has been<lb/> so destructive
                                        over the world,<lb/> besides I have been very
                                        dissat<lb/>isfied with the manner you<lb/> have lately
                                        conducted the<lb/> Occident, you have permitted<lb/> &amp;
                                        published the most <sic>scurilous</sic></p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>articles to be inserted that<lb/> was positively a disgrace to<lb/>
                                        any respectable party, witness<lb/> the article on
                                                  <persName>Mr Wise</persName> of<lb/>
                                        <placeName><sic>Cincinati</sic></placeName>, I declare I
                                        was<lb/> shocked at reading it &amp; then<lb/> it appears
                                        that each of our<lb/> ministers in
                                                  <placeName>Ama.</placeName> Mention<lb/> his best
                                        endeavors to bring his<lb/> fellow into contempt &amp;
                                                  de<add>?</add>,<lb/> why is this, when will
                                        our<lb/> pretended wise men see that in<lb/> endeavoring to
                                        humble their<lb/> fellow, they are using every effort<lb/>
                                        to disgust their laymen. I<lb/> confess that I would rather
                                        be<lb/> without any ministry than be</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>disgraced by such a one as<lb/> your pages exhibit—<add>?</add>
                                        <persName>Mr<lb/> Leeser</persName> put a stop to the<lb/>
                                        scandal you publish to the<lb/> world.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose the Bank of St Thomas<lb/> Bill No 9717
                                        on <persName>J C Whitmore</persName>
                                        <placeName>New York</placeName> for $23.53; for the
                                        following;<lb/> received from this congregation<lb/> for
                                        advertisements omitted last<lb/> remittance $6—<lb/> one
                                        year subscription<lb/> to Occident for <date>1857</date>
                                        for<lb/> 9<add>?</add> subscribers  9—<lb/> one year for two
                                        for <date>1858</date> 6.—<lb/> received from
                                                  <persName>Piza</persName> for<lb/> your
                                        a/c  3<lb/> Bill $23.53 $24—<lb/> premium .47<lb/> $24—</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>which balances our account.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My wife joins with kind<lb/> regardes &amp; to
                                                  <persName>Mr. &amp; Mrs Florence</persName><lb/>
                                        whom we hope are in the<lb/> enjoyment of health</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Yours truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>You will remark that <sic>their</sic><lb/> is one Subscriber less
                                        than<lb/> last year, a party who left<lb/> the
                                                  <placeName>Island</placeName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">In referring to my memo of<lb/> after the Bill was
                                        drawn I find<lb/> I <sic>creditted</sic> you with $—40/100
                                        less<lb/> on the sum recd from the Synagogue<lb/>
                                        authorities, which will be remembered<lb/> the next
                                        remittance</p>
                    </body>
